<header>Agent Installers</header>
<sub-head page='installers'></sub-head>
<hr />
<nav-bar />
<hr />
 
<p> An agent is represented in the information Agency by a persistent software
    object.  In order for the agency to know about an Agent and direct
    requests like <code> http://localhost:8888/Agent/home </code> to an
    <code>Agent</code>, the agent must be "installed," which creates the
    corresponding software object.

</p><p> When the Agency is started, it looks in the Agency's <code><a href='START-UP.html'>START-UP.html</a></code> and installs any agents found
    there.  (Like all agent files, the original file found in the
    &AGENT:name;agent's home directory, in this case
    &piaDIR;/Agents/&AGENT:name;/ can be overridden by local files in
    &usrDIR;/Agents/&AGENT:name;/.)

</p><p> Other agents can be installed using this form which contains ``canned''
    install forms for various agents.  You can paste sections out of this file
    into your own <code> START-UP.html </code> file.  When you design a new
    agent, you can add a default install form to this page.

</p><p> There is also a <a href='install-agent'>generic agent installation form</a>
    which allows you to type in the name an type of an agent directly.

</p><h3>Contents:</h3>

<ul>
  <li> <a href='#agents'>Standard Agents</a> (what most users want)
  </li><li> <a href='#DOFS'>Document-Oriented File Systems</a>
  </li><li> <a href='#generic'>Generic form</a>
</li></ul>

<hr />
<h3><a name='agents'>Standard Agents</a></h3>
<dl> 
  <dt> <a name='View'>View agent</a>
       <if><agent-running name='View'></agent-running>
           <then><em>installed</em></then><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       name: <input name='agent' value='View' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  </dt><dt> <a name='Proxie'>Proxie agent</a>
       <if><agent-running name='Proxie'/>
           <then><em>installed</em></then><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       name: <input name='agent' value='Proxie' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
       <dl>
	 </dt><dt> <a name='History'>History agent</a>
	      <if><agent-running name='History' />
	          <then><em>installed</em></then><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/Admin/install-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value='Install' />
	      name: <input name='agent' value='History' />
	      home: <input name='home-dir' value='./Proxie/History' />
	      </form></dd></else></if>
	 </dt><dt> <a name='Toolbar'>Toolbar agent</a>
	      <if><agent-running name='Toolbar' />
	          <then><em>installed</em></then><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value='Install' />
	      name: <input name='agent' value='Toolbar' />
	      path: <input name=path' value='Proxie' />
	      </form></dd></else></if>
	 </dt><dt> <em>Note:</em>
	 </dt><dd> The following are properly sub-agents of Toolbar, but are
	      currently implemented as sub-agents of Proxie in order to get
	      around a naming bug.  <dl>
		<dt> <a name='remoteTools'>remoteTools agent</a>
		     <if><agent-running name='remoteTools'>
		     </agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then>
		     <else>
		<dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
		     <input type='submit' value='Install' />
		     name: <input name='agent' value='remoteTools' />
		     type: <input name="type" value="Proxie/Toolbar" />
		     path: <input name="path" value="Proxie/Toolbar" />
		     home: <input name="home-dir" value="Proxie/remoteTools" />
		     </form></dd></else></if>
		</dt><dt> <a name='fileTools'>fileTools agent</a>
		     <if><agent-running name='fileTools'>
		     </agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then><else>
		<dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
		     <input type='submit' value='Install' />
		     name: <input name='agent' value='fileTools' />
		     type: <input name="type" value="Proxie/Toolbar" />
		     path: <input name="path" value="Proxie/Toolbar" />
		     home: <input name="home-dir" value="Proxie/fileTools" />
		     </form></dd></else></if>
	      </dt></dl>
	 </dd><dt> <a name='Cache'>Cache agent</a> (keeps a copy of every external
	      doc...) 
	      <if><agent-running name='Cache'>
	      </agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then><else>
	 <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
	      <input type='submit' value='Install' />
	      name:<input name='agent' value='Cache' />
	      path: <input name=path' value='Proxie' /><br />
	      (could add more options here, like update frequency: always, never,
	      once,...) 
	      </form> </dd></else></if>
       </dt></dl>

  </dt><dt> <a name='Demo'>Demo</a>
       Active Document Demonstration and Test agent
       <if><agent-running name='Demo'></agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then><else>
  <dd> <FORM action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       name: <input name='agent' value='Demo' />
       </FORM></dd></else></if>

  </dt><dt> <a name='Swifty'>Swifty</a>
       (from tutorial: illustrates how to create an agent)
       <if><agent-running name='Swifty' />
           <then><em>installed</em></then><else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       name:<input name='agent' value='Swifty' /><br />
       </form> </dd></else></if>

</dt></dl>

<hr />
<h3><a name='DOFS'>Document-Oriented File Systems</a></h3>
Provides basic file browsing capabilities.
<dl>
  <dt> <a name='dofs'>the DOFS agent</a>
  </dt><dd> <if><agent-running name='DOFS'>
       </agent-running><then><em>is already running, as it should be.</em></then>
       <else> Really needs to be running, or lots of things won't work.
       <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install NOW!' />
       name:<input name='agent' value='DOFS' />
       </form></else></if><p>

  <dt> <a name='My'>DOFS/My</a> is no longer needed:
  </dt><dd> <a href='/~/'>/~/</a> (the <a href='/ROOT'>ROOT</a> agent's data
       directory) has replaced it.
       
  </dd><dt> <a name='PIA'>DOFS/PIA</a>
       <if><agent-running name='PIA'></agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then>
       <else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='PIA' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='&piaDIR;/Doc' />
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  </dt><dt> <a name='PIA'>DOFS/Doc</a>
       <if><agent-running name='Doc'></agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then>
       <else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Doc' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='&piaDIR;/Doc' />
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  </dt><dt> <a name='Home'>DOFS/Home</a> (possible security hole)
       <if><agent-running name='Home'></agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then>
       <else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Home' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='~/' />
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  </dt><dt> <a name='Root'>DOFS/Root</a> (probable security hole)
       <if><agent-running name='Root'></agent-running><then><em>installed</em></then>
       <else>
  <dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Root' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='/' />
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       </form></dd></else></if>
  </dt><dt> Generic DOFS form:
  </dt><dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       name:<input name='agent' value='Name' />
       type:<input name='type' value='DOFS' /><br />
       root:<input name='root' value='/complete/path/' />
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       </form><form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>

</form></dd></p></dd></dl>

<hr />

<h3><a name='generic'>Generic Form for installing an agent</a></h3>

<dl>
  <dt>
  </dt><dd> <form action='/&AGENT:name;/install-agent' method='POST'>
       <input type='submit' value='Install' />
       <b>Name:</b><input name='agent' value='' />
       <b>Type:</b><input name='type' value='' />
       </form>

       You can leave the <b>Type</b> blank and it will default to the name.
       If your agent needs non-default options, you'll have to create your own
       form.
</dd></dl>

